oai_dc:dc.dc:title: USS Nashville
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Launched in 1895, the Nashville was the only gunboat of its class. Along with firing the first shot in the Spanish-American War, it also captured four Spanish vessels and assisted in cutting the Atlantic telegraph cable between Cuba and Spain. Here it is in Key West, Florida in 1898.
